19 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
20 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
21 A. The Oklahoma Legislature finds that:
22 1. To maintain strong economic growth and to improve the
23 quality of life of its citizens, the electrical generation capacity
24 within the State of Oklahoma must increase significantly over time;
Req. No. 13336 Page 1

1 2. Along with our traditional abundance of natural gas
2 generation, the growth of various renewable energy projects could
3 significantly expand the renewable energy footprint which could
4 potentially impact agriculture production;
5 3. There are strategies for both the siting and construction of
6 these renewable energy projects that could minimize this impact on
7 farming and ranching and in some cases assist in improving overall
8 agriculture productivity; and
9 4. It is in the interest of the public that the State of
10 Oklahoma develop a legislative strategy designed to maintain
11 agricultural productivity along with renewable energy development in
12 a way that works in harmony with farming and ranching.
13 B. It is the intent of the Legislature that policies designed
14 to provide for new renewable energy generation construction also
15 supports the agriculture industry to be developed in the future.
